        "title": "IntStream.sum() exception handling",
        "body": "<p>Why does <code>IntStream.sum()<\/code> return an int value? Is it some conceptual mistake? When creating a stream from the exemplary array:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>int A[] = {2^31-5, 2, 2, 2};\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Sum of all elements exceeds the maximal integer value, but no exception is thrown. Does anybody know how to prevent such situations?<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 26532184,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "java-8"
        ],
        "score": 1,
        "accepted_answer_id": 26533797,
